verbose_text: The expression of functionally active complement receptor 3 by the lower, but not the upper, female genital tract mucosa; together with data indicating that gonococcal adherence to and invasion of primary cervical epithelial cells and tissue are predominately aided by this surface expressed host molecule; provide one explanation for asymptomatic / subclinical gonococcal cervicitis.
evidence: expression of functionally active complement receptor 3
